crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The code snippet imports the tkinter library and attempts to determine the location of the tkinter library file. It first checks if the system is running PyPy, and if so, it sets the TKINTER_LIB variable to the path of the tkinter library file for PyPy. If the system is not running PyPy, it sets the TKINTER_LIB variable to the path of the tkinter library file for CPython. If the tkinter library is compiled directly into Python, the TKINTER_LIB variable is set to None. Finally, it stores the version of tkinter in the tk_version variable.
